# Global RTD Sensor Market 2024-2030: Market, Size and Growth



The growth has been on the rise in the global market for RTD sensors over the past couple of years due to the ever-increasing expansion in the demand for accurate and reliable temperature measurements across all industries. The demands increased more mainly because RTDs are known to be highly precise, to have high stability, and to cover a very wide range of temperature measurement. This report presents a full research on the global RTD sensor market focused on the size, growth trends, key drivers, challenges, and outlook in the future.

# 1. Introduction to RTD Sensors
RTD sensors are temperature sensors with an operating principle based on the change of electrical resistance of some metals with temperature. The most common metals used in RTD sensors are platinum, copper, and nickel; however, platinum is the most dominant material because it is stable and accurate to a wide operating range of temperature. RTD sensors provide high precision and repeatability.

# 2. Market Size and Growth
The global RTD sensor market was around USD 1.2 billion in 2023 and is further estimated to grow with a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of around 6.5% from 2024 to 2030. The main reason underpinning the growth in the market is industrial process automation. Some of the other factors are increased demand for temperature-sensitive products in the food and beverage industry and increasing adoption of electric vehicles (EVs), requiring accurate temperature monitoring for batteries and their power systems.

